      {
        "id": 3381239,
        "name": "D@vid K@ntr0witz",
        "username": "David_K2",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/david_k2/{size}/2340_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-03-27T22:25:35.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"6\" data-topic=\"178168\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"178168\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Are La Forest and La Foret the same vineyard?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Yes, just variant spellings.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Does anyone use La Forest other than Dauvissat? It seems like everyone else uses For\u00eat or For\u00eats.</p>",
