      {
        "id": 3381426,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-03-28T05:41:55.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"8\" data-topic=\"178168\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"6\" data-topic=\"178168\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"178168\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Are La Forest and La Foret the same vineyard?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Yes, just variant spellings.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Does anyone use La Forest other than Dauvissat? It seems like everyone else uses For\u00eat or For\u00eats.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>A couple show up on CT, but few enough that they could simply be data entry errors by users.</p>",
